race.comment: EXPRESS STAR (6) has chased gamely to the line in three runs to date and looks ready to peak now stepping up in trip. Well placed to shed the maiden tag. CAVASCOT (11) has been honest without threatening dominant winners but strips fitter third-up and finds a very winnable race. TWILIGHT STEPS (21) was solid last start over this track and trip and is drawn to get every chance. In the mix again. BOLD BEAUTY (16) was plain fresh but is capable of sharp improvement second-up. Keep safe. KOJAK (2) Tarzino gelding from the stakes-winning mare Sierra Beel. Ran fifth at recent trial.  Watch the market for any moves.
